Vice President Kamala Harris spoke with President Alejandro Giammattei of Guatemala to discuss their commitment to working together and expanding partnerships for the benefit of the people in the region. They addressed the risks faced by individuals leaving their homes and making the dangerous journey to the United States, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic. Vice President Harris provided an update on the United States' efforts to increase humanitarian assistance to Guatemala, Honduras, and El Salvador. They also agreed to explore opportunities to create jobs, improve conditions, promote transparency, and combat crime in Guatemala and the region. Both leaders agreed to collaborate on promoting economic development, leveraging technology, strengthening climate resilience, and creating conditions that expand opportunities in their home countries to address the root causes of migration to the United States. Vice President Harris expressed gratitude to President Giammattei for his efforts in securing Guatemala's southern border.